Citation.sTitle: Determination and correlation of the solubility for diosgenin in alcohols solvents
Citation.sAbstract: Using a laser monitoring technique, the solubility data of diosgenin in ethanol, 1-propanol, 1-butanol, isobutyl alcohol, tert-butanol, 1-pentanol and iso-octyl alcohol were measured over the temperature range from (290.15 to 330.15) K at atmospheric pressure. Its corresponding (solid +  liquid) equilibrium data will provide essential support for industrial design and further theoretical studies. From the experimental data, the solubility of diosgenin in ethanol, 1-propanol, 1-butanol, isobutyl alcohol, tert-butanol, 1-pentanol and iso-octyl alcohol were found to increase with increasing  temperature and decrease with the increase of the polarity of the alcohols solvents. The Apelblat equation, the ideal model and the lamda-h equation were used to correlate the solubility data; the results  showed that the three models mentioned above agreed well with the experimental data.
